				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Quick question about aggro<a name="20815"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 12 04 3:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm just getting to the point where I'm starting to think about pulling hard LDoNs. I've done a lot of normals, trying to get used to the different maps/mob types/pathing etc., and every room I pull, I think &quot;How would I pull this if it were a hard?&quot;
<br />

<br />
I sometimes come across rooms with like 6-8 mobs in it, so my question is this: 
<br />

<br />
Lets say there are 3 mobs relatively near each other. Mob 1 is in aggro range of Mob 2, and Mob 2 is in aggro range of Mob 3, but Mob 1 isn't in aggro range of Mob 3. If I were to mez Mob 1, Mob 2 would come after me, but would Mob 3? If so, I really have no idea how I would pull rooms with more than 3 mobs in them in a hard.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance for the help <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
